Package ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.editors

Interface Navigator

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractNavigator, HTMLNavigator, JavaScriptNavigator, PropertyNavigator, TileSetNavigator
public interface Navigator
Navigators build a list of NavigationPoints that allow quick navigation between semantically significant sections of edited source code. The generated list can be displayed to the user in a special pane, allowing the user to quickly jump between these significant locations.
Since:
3.0
See Also:
CodeEditor.setNavigator(ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.editors.Navigator), NavigationPoint

  • Method Details

    • install

      void install​(CodeEditor editor)
      Called when this navigator is about to become the navigator for a code editor. This allows the navigator to perform editor-specific initialization. For example, it might install a custom Highlighter.
      Parameters:
      editor - the editor that this navigator is being added to

    • uninstall

      void uninstall​(CodeEditor editor)
      Called when this navigator is about to be removed from a code editor. This allows the navigator to reverse editor-specific initialization. For example, it might remove a previously installed Highlighter.
      Parameters:
      editor - the editor that this navigator is being removed from
      See Also:
      install(ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.editors.CodeEditor)
